.SH NAME
dotty-dotfiles-status - Report the link state of the dotfiles tree without changing it.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty dotfiles status [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Walk the repository's home/ tree against $HOME and report each entry: ok
(linked correctly), missing (link would be created), stale (a symlink
pointing elsewhere), or conflict (a real file in the way).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for status


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	dotfiles repository (default: found via $REPOS_DIR)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty dotfiles status
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-dotfiles(1)\fP
